<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14196e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14196e">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14196e"> 196(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mira Omicron / long period variables </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: A red giant star, Mira Omicron is the brightest long-period pulsating variable star in the Cetus constellation. Mira&apos;s variability was recorded for the first time in 1596 by the Dutch astronomer David Fabricius. In 1638 Johannes Helvetius gave the star its Latin name: Mira, meaning &lsquo;wonderful.&rsquo; Johann Bayer included it on his star atlas and named it Omicron Ceti. </mm> </dd></dl>
